[[File:LoadingScreen_Support.png|thumb|A loading screen showing VRRat with a link to a support page.]]
'''Loading Screens''' are a series of intermittent scenes that are shown when loading into the client or [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|worlds]]. It displays helpful tips about VRChat, as well as display a download progress bar.

== Client ==
The loading screen scene consists of a teal void with bubble-like particles floating around. In the center of the view point is a graphic showing various tips. Underneath, displays the percentage of the world downloading progress. Below that, shows a "Return to Home" button to return to the user's [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Home world|home world]]. If the user is loading their home world, and they click the Return to Home button, it will load the [[VRChat Home]] instead.

After downloading, the loading screen will display the thumbnail of the world with a load indicator below it. The load indicator states progress in this order: 

* "'''Initializing World...'''", "'''Connecting...'''", "'''Joining...'''", and "'''Almost Done!'''"<small>{verify}</small> if the loading takes too long.

While in VR, you are able to see a mirrored version of the loading screen by looking behind.

